Description:
Auction This Saturday 26th of October at 2.30pm
Renovated and radiant, this elegant three bedroom plus studio Californian bungalow presents stylish accommodation in a convenient locale. Beyond the classic leadlight window façade, a hallway lined with timber floorboards accesses three spacious bedrooms and a welcoming lounge boasting a traditional open fireplace. The modern kitchen/meals is fully appointed with stainless steel appliances and extends via stacker servery window and doors to a vast all-weather alfresco deck overlooking tranquil landscaped gardens. The studio alternatively repurposes as a comfortable fourth bedroom (split system air conditioner) while a pristine laundry, bathroom and second toilet complete sparkling amenities. Ducted heating, evaporative air conditioning and off street parking round out an exciting offering. Centrally placed with schools, parks, the Merri Creek Trail and tram at your fingertips, families, professionals and investors will be suitably impressed.
Insights: 37 Nicholson Street, Coburg VIC 3058 was last sold in 2019 and 49 other 4 bedroom house in Coburg have recently been sold.

Description:
Deceased Estate - Ready for Its Next Chapter!
This charming, 3-4 bedroom, Californian Bungalow is ready to be restored and rejuvenated to bring it back to life.
On a great, flat block the typical floor plan contains: 3 bedrooms coming off central hallway. Separate living/dining or potential for 4th bedroom. Neat bathroom with bath. Updated kitchen with s/steel appliances. Separate laundry. Front driveway for OSP. Great backyard with garden shed. Some period features including: high ceilings, hardwood floors & 2, decorative fireplaces.
Walking distance to Sydney Road shops, cafes and tram. Approx 650m to Coburg station & leisurely access to Upfield bike bath.
Plan your future here!

Description:
Beautiful Home in Ideal Locale
In one of the most sought after pockets in Coburg lies this well maintained and beautiful home. Perfect for a first home buyer or investor looking for a great return. North facing giving you an abundance of natural light. This stunning property has more than enough room for you to create new memories in.
A generous home on an allotment of 331sqm (approx.). Featuring four generously size bedrooms, master bedroom with a walk-in wardrobe and ensuite. Serviced by central bathroom with a bath tub and separate toilet. Well-equipped kitchen offers an abundance of cupboard/bench space and gas cook top, perfect for any aspiring master-chef. With open plan kitchen/dining area which is perfect for entertaining family and friends. Adjoining to the rear yard which is ready for you to create the garden of your dreams.
Other features of this character filled home include separate laundry with linen closet, ducted heating throughout and electric roller shutters at the front of the property, either way you will enjoy calling this place home.
In a first-class location, this home is within walking distance to the vibrant Sydney Road which gives you access to all the cafes, restaurants, boutiques that are on offer and providing easy access to public transport such as the number 19 Tram and Coburg train station which takes you all the way through to the heart of the city. Coburg Senior High School and various private schools just a stones through away, along with Coburg Lake.
Insights: 12 Sheffield Street, Coburg VIC 3058 was last sold in 2019 and 49 other 4 bedroom house in Coburg have recently been sold.

Description:
Pretty Californian, Perfect Entertainer
From its pretty façade through spacious interiors and entertainer's gardens this three bedroom Californian Bungalow offers charismatic living. Grandly proportioned with lofty ceilings, splendid open fireplace and striking leadlight windows this inviting home features bedrooms serviced by a bright central bathroom, and a spacious living domain where a kitchen diner, large enough to host a hoard, spills to a deck and gardens offering relaxed indoor-outdoor entertaining. Electrolux/Asko appliances grace the well-ordered island kitchen while the lounge provides an inviting space in which to unwind. Add to this ducted heating, split system air-conditioner, ceiling fans and OSP and all set in a community spirited locale that enjoys the convenience of Batman & Coburg Railway Stations, Coburg North Village shopping precinct, Coburg North Primary School, Sydney Road shops and cafés, Farmer's Market, Coburg Lake, and the Merri Creek bike trail.

Description:
Classic Charm, Contemporary Style and Extended Versatility!
Retaining the allure of its Californian Bungalow origins, this home has been transformed into a family oasis of quality and flexibility with its cleverly expanded floorplan and impressive features list - all in a wonderfully quiet and convenient Coburg neighbourhood. Beyond the rendered facade, enjoy the home's immaculate interior boasting a large master bedroom including fitted WIR and stylish ensuite complete with steam shower, two additional bedrooms (BIRs) and main central bathroom with spa bath. Add to this spacious open-plan living and dining areas complemented by a well-appointed kitchen with Smeg cooking appliances and Fisher & Paykel double dish drawer. Refrigerated cooling and ducted heating provide all-seasons comfort along with the reassurance of an alarm system and motorized security shutters all-round, plus solar power, laundry/third WC, floor-to-ceiling tiles (both bathrooms) and high ceilings throughout. Step outside to discover a private entertainer's backyard with wide undercover patio and BBQ area as well as a handy storage shed and the added advantage of two-car front off-street parking. A short stroll to O'Hea Street buses, Coburg North Primary School and the open spaces of Harmony Park, it's also close to popular Coburg North Village Shopping Centre, as well as easy access Batman Station and Sydney Road trams.

Description:
Meticulous & Majestic
In one of Coburg's best pockets is this majestic newly built home that has been meticulously planned and constructed to the highest quality. Within walking distance to Coburg Lake, Upfield bike path, Primary and Secondary Schools, Coburg leisure centre, Sydney Road, Bell Street and Louisa Street each with a large choice of restaurants, cafes and supermarkets to choose from. As for public transport you have Sydney road tram (no 19), Coburg and Moreland Train Station and the bus interchange on the corner of Bell Street and Sydney Road with five different buses routes (no 513, 527, 534, 561 & 904).
Boasting high ceilings throughout, downstairs includes a guest master bedroom with double glazed windows, walk in wardrobe and your own ensuite. A light filled open plan dining/living area with European Oak timber flooring and adjoining onto the stunning kitchen. Featuring 900mm Smeg appliances including dishwasher, double sink with Pendent lighting, triple pantry, soft closing drawers, 60mm Sierra Leone stone bench tops with a waterfall finish and complemented by the tiled splash back. Leading out through the large sliding doors and onto your own private decking area, overlooking the landscaped rear yard with beautiful plants such as magnolias, azaleas and camellias.
Heading upstairs you will find three generous size bedrooms all with built in wardrobes, while the master bedroom includes its own private ensuite. All bedrooms are serviced by an immaculate central bathroom with floor to ceiling tiles, stand-alone bathtub and a separate shower with a double shower head.
Complementing this absolutely beautiful home is a double garage, separate laundry, powder room, alarm/intercom system, matte black fixtures throughout and Zoned Mitsubishi refrigerated cooling and heating.
This exceptional home is exactly what you have been looking for!
Insights: 51 Loch Street, Coburg VIC 3058 was last sold in 2019 and 49 other 4 bedroom house in Coburg have recently been sold.

Description:
Quality and Class with Unbeatable Convenience
In a secure modern complex with De Chene Reserve and Merri Creek trails across the road, this third-floor apartment presents a terrific entry into Coburg or outstanding inner-urban investment opportunity. Impeccably-presented throughout, the home's as-new interior comprises two double bedrooms (both with built-in robes) and sleek central bathroom with stone-top vanity and floor-to-ceiling tiles, light-filled open living/dining area leading out to a fully-undercover balcony with leafy outlook. Add to this a classy kitchen with soft-close drawers, tiled splashbacks, stainless steel cooking appliances and dishwasher. Other highlights include panel heaters, spotless carpet, modern full-size laundry, plus lift access to secure entry foyer, undercover parking space and storage cage. City-bound trams at your doorstep, it's also close to primary and secondary schools, as well as Sydney Road cafes, restaurants and vibrant shopping precinct. Easy modern living or blue-chip investing!

Description:
AUCTION this Saturday 19th of October at 12pm
With great street presence, a central location and generous proportions, this previously renovated and extended five bedroom plus study period residence provides exceptional family comfort, convenience and flexibility. Enhanced by leadlight entry, decorative high ceilings/rosettes, ornate plasterwork, natural light and polished floorboards, the spacious layout includes multiple living/entertaining zones, over two levels, and large open dining featuring gas coal open fireplace with mirrored timber mantel and cast iron insert. Showcasing Falcon upright range cooker/pyrolytic oven, dishwasher, ample storage and island bench, the kitchen will impress. A covered alfresco zone, large backyard, charming bedrooms, most with built-in-robes, period-inspired bathroom, laundry/storage, ducted heating and off street parking ensure appeal. Close to schools, Sydney Road shops, markets, cafés, train stations and John Fawkner Hospital.

The comfortable interior presents ample scope to add your personal touch. Comprising 2 bedrooms(one with BIR), spacious living and dining, separate kitchen with direct access to a private courtyard, central bathroom with laundry facilities and car space. Description:
Captivating Edwardian-Era Home with a Character All its Own
A beauty defined by its bay windows, distinctive ornamentation and gorgeous gardens all round, this unique period home (c.1915) offers a truly outstanding lifestyle opportunity in a blissfully quiet family-focused Coburg neighbourhood. With well-proportioned rooms and an abundance of natural light, the home's immediately enjoyable interior comprises three genuinely large bedrooms (master with built-in robes) and study/fourth bedroom, contemporary-style central bathroom and separate (second) WC. Add to this an elegant and spacious lounge room and an updated kitchen with ample cupboard space and Bosch dishwasher. Other stand-out features of this one-of-a-kind home include high ornate ceilings, a lovely enclosed veranda, decorative architraves and solid timber floors, gas heating and NBN connection, plus a substantial back garden with lock-up garage (via Selbourne Street) and plenty of room for future expansion (STCA). Walking distance to local primary schools (Coburg West and St Fidelis), public transport options, parks, cafes and shopping precincts, as well as easy access to Citylink/Tullamarine Freeway.

Quaint, Brick Home in Convenient Location!
Check out the potential of this semi-detached two-bedroom residence on a large garden block (436m2 approx) in a heritage streetscape surrounded by classic mid-century homes. With scope to modernize and extend (STCA), the floor plan includes; large living room, two good-sized bedrooms. Neat kitchen/meals room with 'chef's size' free-standing oven. Merri Creek trails and parkland at the end of the street, it's also walking distance to Coburg Lake and swimming pool, Murray Road buses and Coburg High School, as well as easy access to Nicholson Street trams and Coburg Hill Shopping Centre. Walking distance to bus, and approx. 9km to CBD.

Description:
Art Deco at its finest
Beautifully presented and impeccably updated, this period home is positioned on the corner in one of Coburg's most sought after neighbourhood. It provides a wonderful lifestyle choice for young families, professional couples or low-maintenance conscious buyers. Under ornate decorative ceilings, the home's interior sparkles like new, with gleaming timber floorboards enhancing a light and air ambiance throughout. The property offers 3 generous sized bedrooms, serviced by the stylish central bathroom, bright open plan design living/dining area with stylish kitchen and stainless steel appliances. Also featuring off-street parking, lead light windows, central heating, split system air conditioning, open fire place and french doors which opens up to a private decking courtyard. So close to Batman train station, Office Works, Bunnings, Mercy College, Coburg Lake, Coburg North Primary, Harmony Park and all that Sydney Road has to offer, Easy freeway access and only 9kms (approx.) to the city.
Insights: 59 Gaffney St, Coburg VIC 3058 was last sold in 2019 and 146 other 3 bedroom house in Coburg have recently been sold.

Description:
Brightly Refurbished With A Versatile Attic Space
A premier boulevard setting, brightly refurbished interiors and a versatile lined attic space make this two bedroom unit one to watch. In a boutique block of six, this spacious property features open plan living where a gas log fire adds charisma, stylish island kitchen with stainless steel appliances opens to a courtyard garden perfect for entertaining, and a lined attic space keeps versatility at the forefront as a potential living space, home office or additional bedroom. Add to this a chic bathroom with stone topped vanity incorporating laundry facilities, plantation shutters, split system air-conditioner and car space. A prestige location set amongst the community spirited puts vibrant Sydney Road, trams, Moreland Station and Merri Creek parkland trails at your fingertips.

Description:
Elegance, Opulence and Architectural Excellence
A vivid mix of period inspiration and modern innovation, this brand-new residential showpiece presents a remarkable inner-urban lifestyle opportunity with its versatile floorplan, luxurious appointments throughout and meticulous attention to detail. Quality at every turn, the home's lavish interior boasts three spacious bedrooms (one downstairs) all with fitted robes and two equally-luxurious bathrooms - both with marble vanities, recessed cisterns and floor-to-ceiling tiles. Bathed in natural light, the open-plan living/dining area is perfectly complemented by a premium kitchen featuring marble benchtops and splashbacks, top-of-the-range Fisher & Paykel cooking appliances and double dish drawer. Along with zoned ducted heating/refrigerated cooling for all-seasons comfort, the home also includes high square-set ceilings, plantation shutters and engineered oak flooring, video intercom, built-in workstation (second bedroom) and concealed laundry facilities. Step outside to fabulous entertaining deck complete with BBQ (hot/cold water and mains-connected), landscaped gardens front and rear, as well as an oversized double garage (r/c) via ROW. A short stroll to the open spaces of Harmony Park and Coburg North Primary School, local buses and Coburg North Village, it also offers easy access to Melville Road trams, Batman Station and the Upfield Bike Path.
Insights: 151 Ohea Street, Coburg VIC 3058 was last sold in 2019 and 146 other 3 bedroom house in Coburg have recently been sold.

Description:
Magnificent renovated c1930s family home
Fusing period elegance and functional modern luxury, this magnificent 1930s home captures the epitome of family living with a stunning bespoke renovation. It enjoys a quiet yet convenient cul-de-sac address, walking distance to city trams, Sydney Road shops, Merri Creek trail, parklands and schools including Coburg Primary and Coburg High. Past its charming weatherboard façade and established front garden, the leadlight entrance leads to a plush master bedroom with bay windows and a stylish ensuite, generous second bedroom with its own front verandah, two further bedrooms including an optional home office/4th bedroom, and an exquisite central bathroom with a freestanding bath and walk-in shower. Chestnut floors flow into a generous state-of-the-art kitchen boasting premium Smeg and Miele appliances, and deluxe open plan living and dining zones that flow through bi-fold glass doors to a private sun soaked entertaining courtyard, veggie garden, separate workshop/studio with covered outdoor BBQ area and off-street parking for 2 cars via ROW access (remote roller door). This warm & inviting home boasts a fresh light-filled interior with loads of features - oversized laundry, ducted heating & cooling, soaring ceilings, built-in robes, a sound system, a security system, plantation shutters, linen storage, loft storage & more. A true family home that is sure to impress. Nelson Alexander Pty Ltd
Insights: 18 Younger Street, Coburg VIC 3058 was last sold in 2019 and 49 other 4 bedroom house in Coburg have recently been sold.

Description:
Unique indoor/outdoor living.
Privately secluded on a pristinely landscaped corner block, this renovated three bedroom plus study home offers unique indoor/outdoor family living just moments to Coburg Hill Shopping Centre plus Newlands Primary and Coburg High Schools. A charming red brick exterior is matched within, open plan living flaunting a fully appointed smart kitchen and modern fireplace. The pergola covered alfresco area appreciates a picturesque garden backdrop and favourable aspect to inspire social gatherings. Meanwhile three double bedrooms presents built-in wardrobes, each with outlooks over tranquil gardens or the saltwater swimming pool and entertaining deck. There's also a light filled study with separate entry, split system air conditioner, remote 1.5 car garage, laundry and copious under house storage with cellar potential.
